post_text:
COVID-19 - Coronoavirus
Wiley School District is working closely with local and state officials regarding the Coronavirus. There is the possibility that we may extend our spring break. We will let you know as soon as possible when and if that decision is made. I can assure you that our custodial staff is doing an amazing job disinfecting every part of our school. Please know that staff and student safety is our number one priority.

According to CDE here are the most recent guidelines with regards to the coronavirus:

A single confirmed case within the school requires a closure of 72 hours. A second confirmed case within the school within 30 days requires an additional 72 hour closure. A 3rd confirmed case would require the school to be closed for 14 days.

You will be notified via our phone/text system with relevant information.

State Wrestling Send-Off
Wiley Cheerleaders will be holding a send-off for our four state wrestling qualifiers on Wednesday, February 19th at 11 a.m. in the commons area. Wear your Rivals wear if you have any! If any classes want to prepare cards or signs for the athletes, please get them to me by Wednesday morning so we can have everything ready for the send-off. Our athletes love this! Remember it is wrestling and the boys must make weight for three straight days so no snacks or drinks please. The Wiley Booster Club will be preparing small goodie bags filled with items the boys can have. Help us show our support for their hard work and achievements so far this season!

CALL FOR NOMINATIONS FOR SCHOOL BOARD ELECTION, NOVEMBER 5, 2019

Wiley School District is Seeking Nominations for one (1) Member-at-Large Seat

Nomination petitions may be obtained at the
Wiley School District office, 510 Ward St., Wiley, CO 81092
Monday-Thursday, 8am - 4pm

To be qualified, a candidate must have been a registered elector and a resident
of the school district for at least twelve consecutive months before the election.

Completed Petitions must be submitted no later than
11:00 am on Friday, August 30, 2019
